All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BasicECA
Utility class for elementary cellular automata (ECA), Wolfram codes 0-255
CayleyDickson
Used to multiply hypercomplex numbers using the Cayley-Dickson algorithm, as well as compare Cayley-Dickson solutions, produces individual multiplication tables, sets of all tables of a given degree, and a recursive version for individual unit vectors
Complex
Complex number class
ConsoleDashboard
Text output for the GUI
ECAasMultiplication
Manages ECAMdeep, ECAMpostProcessing, and ECAMspecific, contains the heart of the project in generalWolframCode() and multiplicativeSolutionOutput()
ECAasMultiplication.whichMultTableNames
Names of the various multiplication tables
ECAMdeep
Exhaustively searches sets of all Wolfram codes of various lengths, with various parameters
ECAMoutputSubsections
Subsections of solutions' output from ECAMpostProcessing, trimmed to size for display
ECAMpostProcessing
Secondary processing of solutions found in ECAasMultiplication, Multiplications B and C, generates output of a ValidSolution, generates the polynomial
ECAMspecific
Main algorithm, Multiplications A, brute force hypercomplex multiplication validating a set of permutations.
Examples
Contains a few examples using the algorithm, one with a class 4 focus, one with an additive rule focus, and a version of Conway's Life
Fano
Uses the Fano plane to generate 480 octonion multiplication tables
GaloisFields
Generates discrete Galois multiplication and addition tables
HTMLdashboard
This outputs the HTML for the imageData solution database,
Main
Standard Java Main class
PermutationsFactoradic
Utility class that includes permutations, factoradics, composition of permutations, array insertions, and gray codes
RuleImageCollection
Collects images of valid ECA solutions and writes to file
SwingBinaryFactorLayers
Each cell's set of permuted neighborhoods as factors in Multiplications A, layer by layer, layer = numFactors is the result layer
SwingBinaryShadow
The binary shadow is 2 planes, one is the real component of the output of a solution and the other is the imaginary component, the input is complex and the components get rounded, less than zero is 1 greater than zero is 0
SwingComplexLayers
Multiplications B, complex, just prior to normalization is a neighborhood of complex data than can be interpreted as a components of a vector for that cell
SwingComplexOutput
Multiplications B and C output, seperately
SwingDashboard
GUI control panel, manages the other Swing classes, there is no algorithm logic in the GUI components, that is all in ECAasMultiplication.
SwingLayers
Displays the binary neighborhoods as binary factor layers, displays the non-negative real version of Multiplications B
SwingOutputPanel
Displays the standard additive binary Wolfram code output for single bit and random initial input, as well as non-negative real input
SwingPolyTest
Multiplications B, displays results of the non-negative real output processed with the polynomial from generatePolynomial() rather than multiplying out the whole numFactors-dim partial product table, verifies generatePolynomial()
SwingTextPanel
Swing text output in a form copyable to a clipboard, JARs don't have a default console to output text to
ValidSolution
A solution from ECAMspecific.generalWolframCode() is in this form
